            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#martaf">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><w><expan><abbr>Θ</abbr><ex>εοῖς</ex></expan></w> <w><expan><abbr>Κ</abbr><ex>ατακθονίοις</ex></expan></w> <w><expan><abbr>ἱ</abbr><ex>ερόν</ex></expan></w>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested"><name>Ζωτικὸς</name></persName> <w>πατήρ</w>
                    <lb n="3"/><w>ἰδίῳ</w> <w>τέκνῳ</w> <w>μνή<lb n="4" break="no"/>μης</w> <w>χάριν</w> <w>ἐποίη<lb n="5" break="no"/>σεν</w>, <w>ὃς</w> <w>ἔζησεν</w> <w>ἔ<surplus>ε</surplus><hi rend="ligature">τη</hi></w>
                    <lb n="6"/><g ref="#ivy-leaf">❦</g> <num value="27">κ<supplied reason="undefined" evidence="previouseditor">η</supplied></num> <supplied reason="undefined" evidence="previouseditor"><g ref="#ivy-leaf">❦</g></supplied>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus" resp="#martaf">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text based on photographs</note></app>
                    <app loc="line 2"><note>Biscari, Torremuzza, Franz: Ἰ(ούλιος) Ζωτικὸς; Ferrara, Kaibel, Korhonen: Ζωτικὸς</note></app>
                    <app loc="line 3"><note>Biscari, Ferrara, Kaibel, Korhonen τέκνῳ; Torremuzza, Franz: τέκνῃ</note></app>
                    <app loc="line 5"><note>ΕΕΤΗ lapis (although Korhonen reports FFTH, considering this linguistic interference; the reading is unclear from photograph due to modern repainting of letters)</note></app>
                    <app loc="line 6"><note>Biscari, Torremuzza, Ferrara, Franz, Kaibel could see a Η and a second ivy leaf at line end, now lost.</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>Sacred to the subterranean deities. Zotikos, the father, made it for the sake of the memory for his own child, who lived for 27 years.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="#martaf">
                <p>Sacro alle divinità sotterranee. Zotico, il padre, ha realizzato per la memoria di suo figlio, che visse 27 anni.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#martaf">
                <p> This pagan epitaph is influenced by Latin: in addition to the expression <foreign xml:lang="grc">Θ(εοῖς) Κ(αταχθονίοις) ἱ(ερόν)</foreign> (modelled on <foreign xml:lang="la">D(iis) M(anibus) s(acrum)</foreign>), an unusual structure for Sicilian Greek inscriptions occurs, in which the invocation to the underworld spirits is followed by the name of the dedicant (often with an attribute), by the name of the deceased in dative, by the dedication verb and by the age of the deceased (see Korhonen 2004: 88). In this case, the relative pronoun introduces the age of the deceased with a <foreign xml:lang="la">costructio ad sensum</foreign> since the gender of the referent (<foreign xml:lang="grc">τέκνον</foreign>) and the relative pronoun do not correspond. The use of <foreign xml:lang="grc">τέκνον</foreign> to indicate the deceased, who died at the age of 27, is also peculiar: on the use of <foreign xml:lang="grc">τέκνον</foreign> in other epitaphs from Catania, generally referring to children, see IMusCatania 67 = <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001306">ISic001306</ref>, IMusCatania 140 = <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003260">ISic003260</ref>. On the use of <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἴδιος</foreign> as a possessive pronoun, see also IG 14.485 = <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001308">ISic001308</ref>.</p>
            </div>
